()🔹ResourceObject kya hai?
👉 ResourceObject ek representation object hai,
👉 Simple me:-
“External system (AD, LDAP, DB, SAP) ka ek account/object ka data hold karta hai”
🔥 Simple Hinglish:-
👉
“Target system (jaise Active Directory) ka user data SailPoint me lane ke liye ResourceObject use hota hai”
“Jab SailPoint bahar ke system se user data uthata hai, wo pehle ResourceObject me aata hai”

🔥 🔹 Ye karta kya hai?
1️⃣ External data hold karta hai
👉 Jaise:-
username
email
roles
groups
--------------------------------------------
🔹 2️⃣ Aggregation me ResourceObject ka use:-
👉 Kya hota hai?
👉 Jab SailPoint external system (AD/LDAP/DB) se data pull karta hai
toh woh ResourceObject me hi hold hota hai.
🔥 Real Flow:-
Connector AD se data laata hai
Har record ke liye ek ResourceObject banta hai
Usme attributes fill hote hain
🔹 Example:-
👉 AD se data aaya:-
Field	        Value
sAMAccountName:-rahul
mail:-------rahul@gmail.com
👉 ResourceObject me convert:-
nativeIdentity = rahul
email = rahul@gmail.com
department = IT
------------------------------------------------------
3️⃣ Provisioning me use hota hai?
👉 Jab tu account create/update/delete karta hai,
toh sailpoint ke through resourceobject hi data leke dusre external system(AD/SAP) me data bhejta hai.

🔥 Real Flow:-
Tu request deta hai (create/update/delete)
ProvisioningPlan banta hai
Connector call hota hai
ResourceObject ban ke data bheja jata hai
🔹 Example:-
()👉 Tu new user create karta hai:-
username = rahul
email = rahul@gmail.com

()👉 Ye ResourceObject banega:-
operation = CREATE
nativeIdentity = rahul
email = rahul@gmail.com
👉 Connector AD me push karega.
------------------------------------------------------
4️⃣ Attribute mapping karta hai:-
👉 External → SailPoint mapping:-
👉 External fields ko SailPoint ke fields me convert karta hai

🔥 Problem samajh:-

👉 AD me field:-
sAMAccountName

👉 SailPoint me:-
name

👉 Direct match nahi hai ❌

🔥 Solution → Mapping
👉 ResourceObject ke through mapping hoti hai:-
sAMAccountName → name
mail → email

🔹 Example:-
👉 ResourceObject:-
sAMAccountName = rahul
mail = rahul@gmail.com

👉 Mapping ke baad:-
Identity.name = rahul
Identity.email = rahul@gmail.com
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
🔥 🔹 DB me kya store hota hai?
👉 ❌ ResourceObject directly DB me store nahi hota
👉 Ye temporary runtime object hai.
----------------------------------------------------------
🔥 🔹 Andar kya kya hota hai?
📌 1️⃣ Native Identity
getNativeIdentity()
👉 External system ka unique ID
👉 Example:-
CN=rahul,OU=Users,DC=company

📌 2️⃣ Attributes (MOST IMPORTANT)
getAttribute("email")
getAttributes()
👉 Map format me hota hai:-
username = rahul
email = rahul@gmail.com
department = IT

📌 3️⃣ Object Type:-
getObjectClass()
👉 Example:-
account
group

📌 4️⃣ Operation:-
getOperation()
👉 CREATE / MODIFY / DELETE

📌 5️⃣ Status:-
isDisabled()
isDeleted()
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
🔥 1️⃣ ResourceObject Types (Detail me)
👉 Ye decide karta hai ki object kis type ka hai (account, group, etc.)

📌 1. ACCOUNT (Most Important):-
👉 External system ka user account represent karta hai
👉 Aggregation me user data aata hai aur provisioning me account create/update hota hai
🔹 Example:-
AD User: rahul
DB User: rahul_db

👉 Attributes:-
username
email
department

📌 2. GROUP:-
👉 Security group ya distribution group represent karta hai
👉 User ke access control aur membership manage karta hai
🔹 Example:-
IT_Admins
HR_Team
👉 Use:-
Group membership mapping
Entitlement assignment

📌 3. ENTITLEMENT:-
👉 Permissions ya access rights ko represent karta hai
👉 Fine-grained access control ke liye use hota hai
🔹 Example:-
READ_ACCESS
WRITE_ACCESS
EXECUTE_ACCESS

👉 Use:-
Authorization
Policy evaluation

📌 4. ROLE:-
👉 Business/application role represent karta hai
👉 Multiple entitlements ka bundle hota hai

🔹 Example:-
Manager Role
Admin Role

👉 Use:-
RBAC (Role-Based Access Control)

📌 5. CUSTOM OBJECT:-
👉 Jab application ka structure standard nahi hota
👉 Tab custom object banaya jata hai
🔹 Example:-
InvoiceObject
ProjectObject
-------------------------------------------------------
🔥 2️⃣ ResourceObject Status (ALL):-
👉 Ye object ka current state batata hai

📌 1. ACTIVE (Default):-
👉 Account active hai
👉 Login allowed hai

📌 2. DISABLED:-
👉 Account temporarily disabled hai
👉 Login allowed nahi
isDisabled()
setDisabled(true)

📌 3. DELETED:-
👉 Account permanently remove ho gaya
👉 System me exist nahi karta
isDeleted()
setDeleted(true)

📌 4. LOCKED (Indirect):-
👉 Account locked hai (failed login etc.)
👉 Attribute based hota hai

📌 5. EXPIRED:-
👉 Password ya account expire ho gaya
👉 Login restricted hai

📌 6. PENDING / NEW:-
👉 Account create hone wala hai
👉 Provisioning pending hai

📌 7. ENABLED:-
👉 Disabled se wapas active hua
-------------------------------------------------
🔥 3️⃣ Operation Types (Provisioning):-
👉 Ye batata hai kya action perform hoga
Operation	Meaning
CREATE	  new account
MODIFY	   update
DELETE	   remove
ENABLE	   enable
DISABLE	   disable
--------------------------------------------------
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
🔥 🔹 1️⃣ objectType kya hai?
👉 objectType = actual object ka exact type (technical level)
👉 Ye batata hai:
ye object account hai
ya group hai
ya entitlement hai

🔥 🔹 type kya karta hai?
1️⃣ Categorize karta hai
👉 Objects ko group karta hai
admin user
normal user
guest user
👉 manager, 
developer,
 employee, 
 HR, 
 owner — ye sab type ke examples ho sakte hain in
ResourceObject.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
🔥 4️⃣ ResourceObject Methods (FULL LIST):-
()👉 Saare methods ResourceObject (object) pe chalte hain,

------------------------------------------------------
📌 A. Identity / Core Methods
getNativeIdentity():-
👉 External system ka unique identifier return karta hai
👉 Example: username ya DN

setNativeIdentity(String id):-
👉 External ID set karta hai
👉 Provisioning me target account identify karta hai

getObjectClass():-
👉 Object ka type return karta hai (account/group)
👉 Processing logic decide hota hai

setObjectClass(String type):-
👉 Object type set karta hai
👉 Connector ko batata hai kya process karna hai.

------------------------------------------------------
📌 B. Attribute Methods (MOST IMPORTANT):-
getAttribute(String name):-
👉 Specific attribute ka value return karta hai
👉 Mapping aur validation me use hota hai

setAttribute(String name, Object value):-
👉 Attribute value set karta hai
👉 Provisioning me data send karne ke liye use hota hai

getAttributes():-
👉 Saare attributes ka map return karta hai
👉 Debugging aur bulk processing me useful

setAttributes(Map attrs):-
👉 Multiple attributes ek saath set karta hai
👉 Performance optimized approach hai

📌 C. Operation Methods:-
getOperation():-
👉 Current operation return karta hai
👉 Provisioning engine ko guide karta hai

setOperation(Operation op):-
👉 Operation type set karta hai
👉 Connector ko action batata hai

📌 D. Status Methods:-
isDisabled():-
👉 Check karta hai disabled hai ya nahi
👉 True hone par login block

setDisabled(boolean flag):-
👉 Enable/disable karta hai account
👉 Provisioning action control karta hai

isDeleted():-
👉 Check karta hai delete hua hai ya nahi
👉 True hone par object invalid

setDeleted(boolean flag):-
👉 Object ko deleted mark karta hai
👉 Aggregation/provisioning me delete indicate karta hai

📌 E. Metadata Methods:-
getDisplayName():-
👉 User-friendly name return karta hai
👉 UI aur logging me use hota hai

setDisplayName(String name):-
👉 Display name set karta hai
👉 Reporting ke liye useful

getType():-
👉 Object ka higher-level classification return karta hai,
👉 Ye batata hai object kis category ka hai,
👉 Advanced processing me use hota hai.

setType(String type):-
👉 Type define karta hai
👉 Custom logic ke liye use hota hai

📌 F. Utility Methods:-
addAttribute(String name, Object value):-
👉 Existing attributes me naya value add karta hai
👉 Multi-value fields ke liye useful

removeAttribute(String name):-
👉 Attribute remove karta hai
👉 Cleanup ya update me use hota hai

hasAttribute(String name):-
👉 Check karta hai attribute exist karta hai ya nahi
👉 Null-safe coding ke liye use hota hai

📌 G. Schema Methods
getSchema():-
“Jo object ResourceObject represent kar raha hai (account/group/etc.), usi ka schema milega”
👉 Attribute validation ke liye use hota hai

setSchema(Schema schema):-
👉 Schema assign karta hai
👉 Connector ko structure batata hai
